          "content": "\n\nI can't create a Confluence Cloud trial instance for you since that requires signing up through Atlassian's website with your email and agreeing to their terms. But I can get everything else ready.\n\nHere's what you need to do, then I'll wire up the rest:\n\n### You do this (takes 2 minutes):\n\n1. Go to https://www.atlassian.com/software/confluence/try\n2. Sign up for a free trial (use your email)\n3. Once in, create a space called something like \"House Documents\"\n4. Create a page called \"Closing Documents\"\n5. Attach your PDFs to that page\n6. Then generate an API token at https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens\n7. Give me these three values:\n   - Your Confluence site URL (e.g., `https://yourname.atlassian.net`)\n   - Your email (the one you signed up with)\n   - The API token you generated\n\nWhile you're doing that, I'll build the Confluence connector and OpenSearch indexing so it's ready to go the moment you have the credentials. Let me start:",
